    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "HTTP RED Metrics",
      "collapsed": true,
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 14 },
      "panels": [
        {
          "id": 9,
          "type": "text",
          "title": "HTTP RED Guide",
          "description": "Documentation for HTTP RED (Rate, Errors, Duration) metrics",
          "gridPos": { "h": 3, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 15 },
          "options": {
            "mode": "markdown",
            "content": "## HTTP RED Metrics\n\nMonitors HTTP request traffic using the RED method: Rate, Errors, Duration.\n\n- **Request Rate by Route** shows requests per second grouped by HTTP route (e.g., /graphql, /rest/v1/, /api/, /ui/).\n- **Error Rate (5xx)** is the ratio of server errors to total requests. Should be near 0%. Above 1% warrants investigation, above 5% is critical.\n- **Active Requests** shows in-flight HTTP requests. Sustained high values may indicate slow backends or connection pooling issues.\n- **Latency p95/p99** shows response time percentiles. p95 under 100ms is healthy for cached reads.\n\n**Troubleshooting:** High error rates with normal latency often indicate application logic errors. High latency with low error rates suggests database or upstream slowness."
          },
          "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" }
        },
        {
          "id": 10,
          "type": "timeseries",
          "title": "Request Rate by Route",
          "description": "HTTP requests per second grouped by route",
          "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 18 },
          "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" },
              "expr": "sum by(http_route)(rate(http_server_request_duration_seconds_count[$__rate_interval]))",
              "legendFormat": "{{http_route}}",
              "refId": "A"
            }
          ],
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "unit": "reqps",
              "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
              "custom": {
                "lineWidth": 1,
                "fillOpacity": 10,
                "pointSize": 5,
                "showPoints": "auto",
                "spanNulls": false,
                "axisPlacement": "auto",
                "drawStyle": "line",
                "gradientMode": "none",
                "barAlignment": 0,
                "lineInterpolation": "linear",
                "stacking": { "mode": "none", "group": "A" },
                "thresholdsStyle": { "mode": "off" }
              },
              "thresholds": {
                "mode": "absolute",
                "steps": [
                  { "color": "green", "value": null }
                ]
              },
              "mappings": []
            },
            "overrides": []
          },
          "options": {
            "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" },
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": [] }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 11,
          "type": "stat",
          "title": "Error Rate (5xx)",
          "description": "Ratio of 5xx server errors to total HTTP requests",
          "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 6, "x": 12, "y": 18 },
          "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" },
              "expr": "sum(rate(http_server_request_duration_seconds_count{http_response_status_code=~\"5..\"}[$__rate_interval])) / sum(rate(http_server_request_duration_seconds_count[$__rate_interval]))",
              "legendFormat": "Error Rate",
              "refId": "A"
            }
          ],
          "fieldConfig": {
