            "overrides": []
          },
          "options": {
            "tooltip": { "mode": "multi", "sort": "desc" },
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": [] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Per-Type Sync Detail",
      "collapsed": true,
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 15 },
      "panels": [
        {
          "id": 15,
          "type": "text",
          "title": "Per-Type Sync Guide",
          "description": "Documentation for per-type sync metrics",
          "gridPos": { "h": 3, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 16 },
          "options": {
            "mode": "markdown",
            "content": "## Per-Type Sync Detail\n\nBreaks down sync metrics by PeeringDB object type (org, campus, fac, carrier, carrierfac, ix, ixlan, ixpfx, ixfac, net, poc, netfac, netixlan).\n\n- **Sync Duration by Type (p95)** shows which types take the longest to sync. Network (net) and NetworkIxLan (netixlan) are typically the largest and slowest.\n- **Objects Synced per Type** shows how many objects were upserted in the selected time range. Large counts are normal for types like netixlan (~100K+ objects).\n- **Deletes per Type** tracks object removals. Non-zero deletes are normal during sync as PeeringDB data changes.\n- **Fetch/Upsert Errors** shows API fetch failures (upstream PeeringDB issues) and database upsert failures (local issues) separately.\n\n**Troubleshooting:** Use the $type variable to filter to specific types. If one type consistently errors, check the PeeringDB API status page. Upsert errors may indicate schema drift."
          },
          "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" }
        },
