          "description": "Documentation for Go runtime metrics",
          "gridPos": { "h": 3, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 17 },
          "options": {
            "mode": "markdown",
            "content": "## Go Runtime\n\nMonitors the Go application runtime internals.\n\n- **Goroutines** shows the current count of active goroutines. Normal baseline is 10-50 for this application. Sustained increases may indicate goroutine leaks.\n- **Heap Memory** shows memory currently in use by the Go heap. Normal range is 50-200MB depending on cached data. The Go 1.26 Green Tea GC keeps overhead low.\n- **Allocation Rate** shows bytes allocated per second. Spikes correlate with sync operations or high request volume. Sustained high rates increase GC pressure.\n- **GC Goal** shows the target heap size the garbage collector aims for. This is managed by the Go runtime and increases with live data.\n\n**Troubleshooting:** Rising goroutine count without corresponding load increase suggests a goroutine leak. High allocation rate with stable heap suggests good GC throughput. If heap keeps growing, check for memory leaks with pprof."
          },
          "datasource": { "uid": "${datasource}" }
