            "mode": "markdown",
            "content": "## Business Metrics\n\nTracks the actual PeeringDB data stored in the local mirror.\n\n- **Total Objects** is the sum of all PeeringDB object counts across all 13 types. A healthy mirror with current PeeringDB data should show ~500K+ total objects.\n- **Objects by Type** breaks down counts per PeeringDB type. The largest types are typically netixlan (network-to-IXP connections), netfac (network-to-facility), and net (networks).\n- **Object Counts Over Time** shows how counts change over the dashboard time range. Sudden drops indicate sync issues or data loss. Gradual growth is normal as PeeringDB data expands.\n\n**Troubleshooting:** If total objects drops suddenly, check the sync health row for failed syncs. If specific types show zero, check per-type sync errors. Compare counts against https://www.peeringdb.com/apidocs/ meta counts for validation."
